The `previous` frame gets `cool()` called, which decrements `pins` to 0. Since `cooled` is now true, it calls `closeLoadedGeneration()` if no one else has pinned it.

But wait, workers *do* pin it. `WorkerHandle` pins the frame in its constructor.
```java
    WorkerHandle(TimelineFrame frame) {
        this.frame = frame.pin();
        // ...
